gate: OPEN
task: S75-TA4
title: Settings — Load Persisted Local Values on Mount
description: |
  After TA2 and TA3 introduce useLocalSettings hook and persist values,
  the settings screen must correctly initialize all local toggles and selectors
  from persisted values when it mounts (or remounts after navigation).

  Steps:
    1. In settings-screen.tsx — replace the 3 useState(true) initializers:
         objectNames, geolocation, defaultMapScale
       with values read from useLocalSettings():
         const { values, set } = useLocalSettings()
         // use values.local_show_names, values.local_show_geo, values.local_default_zoom

    2. Replace the handleLocalToggle pattern for these 3 with:
         (val) => set('local_show_names', val)   // etc.
       This removes the need for separate local state entirely.

    3. InputRow displayed values for zoom/step:
         eventDisplay:  'x' + values.local_zoom_event
         objectDisplay: 'x' + values.local_zoom_object
         scrollStep:    String(values.local_scroll_step)
       These should be read from useLocalSettings on every render.

    4. Verify settings screen shows the correct persisted values immediately
       on first render after a page reload (no flicker from default → persisted).

    5. Remove the now-redundant useState calls for objectNames, geolocation,
       defaultMapScale from settings-screen.tsx entirely.

acceptance:
  - After toggling "Object names" and navigating away + back, toggle is in correct state
  - After selecting zoom level and refreshing page, zoom selector shows correct value
  - No double-render flash (default then persisted) for any settings control
  - settings-screen.tsx has no useState for objectNames / geolocation / defaultMapScale

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
estimated: 1 hour
dep: S75-TA2, S75-TA3
